@* Integer division (BENCH n°20): value halved by INT division. C# truncates 7/2 to 3; JS `/` yields
   3.5, so the generator must emit Math.trunc(...) -- the "3" the oracle asserts proves it did. Mirrors
   Divide.Blazor's DOM contract: the blank lines between the three siblings are part of the contract
   (Blazor ships them as "\n\n" text nodes; so does the generator; so does divideint.js). *@

<h1 id="title">DivideInt</h1>

<p>Value: <span id="divide-value">@value</span></p>

<button id="halve" @onclick="Halve">Halve</button>

@code {
    private int value = 7;

    private void Halve()
    {
        value = value / 2;
    }
}
